This documentation describes <%= vars.product_full %> (<%= vars.product_abbr %>).
<%= vars.product_short %> currently enables platform teams to curate a single set of brokered services for
use by app teams.

## <a id='overview'></a> Overview

This alpha version of <%= vars.product_abbr %> enables platform teams to register and curate Open Service Broker API (OSBAPI)
compliant service brokers, running anywhere, from a single centralized location.

App teams can then use these brokers to provision services and retrieve credentials through the `pdc` command
line tool (CLI).
The apps can then use these credentials to access the service instances, even if the apps exist across multiple
runtime environments, such as <%= vars.platform_name %> and <%= vars.k8s_runtime_full %>.

<p class="note">
    <strong>Note:</strong> The <%= vars.product_full %> team is especially keen for user feedback on the use of
    credentials by apps.
</p>

## <a id='features'></a> Key Features

<%= vars.product_full %> can:

* Register OSBAPI-compliant brokers
* Provide isolation for services within different app projects
* Create services and access them across multiple runtime environments

